1
00:01:01,437 --> 00:01:03,439
EPISODE 11

2
00:01:03,522 --> 00:01:04,398
You're getting off work late.

3
00:01:04,982 --> 00:01:06,066
There's a shoot tomorrow,

4
00:01:06,150 --> 00:01:07,735
so I had to prepare before I left.

5
00:01:13,949 --> 00:01:15,659
-Excuse me, Chair Kim.
-What?

6
00:01:15,743 --> 00:01:17,119
When might you be available?

7
00:01:17,203 --> 00:01:18,370
Why do you ask?

8
00:01:18,454 --> 00:01:20,122
I think it's time for a new profile photo.

9
00:01:20,206 --> 00:01:22,500
You've been in the media a lot these days.

10
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:24,835
We can talk about that some other time!

11
00:01:34,136 --> 00:01:35,387
The exit passcode is different.

12
00:02:09,964 --> 00:02:12,091
Seol-ah.

13
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,260
We need to get out of here.

14
00:04:01,450 --> 00:04:02,451
That's right.

15
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:04,912
This is where you belong.

16
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,050
-Let's go.
-Okay.

17
00:04:28,394 --> 00:04:31,397
When will the job be finished?

18
00:04:31,981 --> 00:04:33,273
Hurry up.

19
00:04:34,108 --> 00:04:36,986
Get it done before the insurance company
or the police find it.

20
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:39,196
Are you okay?

21
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:42,866
Did you find

22
00:04:43,993 --> 00:04:45,035
what you were looking for?

23
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:47,454
They were all there.

24
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:51,291
The Taemyung pieces,
the ones Chair Kim had switched out,

25
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:54,628
and even my father's painting.

26
00:04:57,256 --> 00:04:59,758
Every family photo I had
was lost in the fire,

27
00:05:00,759 --> 00:05:02,636
but the last memory of my family

28
00:05:03,679 --> 00:05:05,347
was locked inside that vault.

29
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:10,769
I'll never forgive Chair Kim.

30
00:05:12,062 --> 00:05:13,814
I'll make her pay for what she did.

31
00:05:15,357 --> 00:05:16,358
I'll be by your side

32
00:05:17,609 --> 00:05:18,861
the whole way.

33
00:05:42,092 --> 00:05:43,218
Enjoy the auction.

34
00:06:08,786 --> 00:06:09,828
Is everything ready?

35
00:06:41,443 --> 00:06:42,903
SEARCH AND SEIZURE WARRANT
ARREST WARRANT

36
00:06:58,669 --> 00:06:59,920
Untitled by Lee Soo-dam

37
00:07:00,003 --> 00:07:02,756
has been sold to a floor bidder
for 400 million won.

38
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,007
Congratulations.

39
00:07:14,726 --> 00:07:19,106
This unpublished masterpiece
is said to be the final work

40
00:07:19,189 --> 00:07:20,691
by Artist Song Hwan-ju.

41
00:07:21,608 --> 00:07:23,652
Its estimated value
exceeds seven billion won,

42
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:24,903
and it's expected to surpass

43
00:07:24,987 --> 00:07:27,489
the artist's most famous work,
Cheong-myeong.

44
00:07:33,162 --> 00:07:34,246
However,

45
00:07:34,329 --> 00:07:38,125
I will not be putting it up
for auction today.

46
00:07:43,088 --> 00:07:44,548
The reason is that it's not authentic.

47
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:47,342
-What?
-It's not authentic?

48
00:07:49,428 --> 00:07:52,681
This artwork was submitted
through unofficial channels

49
00:07:52,764 --> 00:07:54,224
-What is she saying?
-under the orders of Chair Kim Sun-ae

50
00:07:54,308 --> 00:07:55,684
at Royal Auction.

51
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:58,729
I questioned its authenticity

52
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,772
and sent it
for professional authentication.

53
00:08:00,856 --> 00:08:02,608
-The results showed
-What is she doing?

54
00:08:02,691 --> 00:08:05,027
-the use of an industrial synthetic resin
-Ms. Han!

55
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:06,653
-rather than the natural glue
-What the hell are you doing?

56
00:08:06,737 --> 00:08:09,990
Artist Song typically used
in their collage works.

57
00:08:10,073 --> 00:08:12,201
ART AUTHENTICATION REPORT: FORGERY

58
00:08:23,086 --> 00:08:24,588
Even the signature is different.

59
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:26,715
SIGNATURE COMPARISON ANALYSIS
FORGERY / GENUINE

60
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,550
The character for "hwan," which means
"to shine," in the artist's name

61
00:08:28,634 --> 00:08:30,510
is incorrectly written,
using the "child" radical

62
00:08:30,594 --> 00:08:32,387
instead of the correct "fire" radical.

63
00:08:32,471 --> 00:08:33,722
You idiot!

64
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:36,558
The authentication agency has confirmed

65
00:08:36,642 --> 00:08:40,187
that this piece is a complete forgery.

66
00:08:40,270 --> 00:08:42,105
Get her. Drag her down.

67
00:08:42,189 --> 00:08:43,023
Yes, ma'am.

68
00:08:43,106 --> 00:08:43,941
That crazy…

69
00:08:54,660 --> 00:08:58,330
We've also obtained evidence
that the Taemyung pieces lost in the fire

70
00:08:58,413 --> 00:09:00,916
were also forgeries.

71
00:09:00,999 --> 00:09:03,252
Hey, get her out of here!
What are you doing?

72
00:09:03,335 --> 00:09:05,921
Damn it! No photos!

73
00:09:06,004 --> 00:09:08,674
Then where are the authentic pieces?

74
00:09:16,431 --> 00:09:17,266
As you can see,

75
00:09:17,349 --> 00:09:20,185
she switched them out and stashed them
in her secret storage vault.

76
00:09:20,269 --> 00:09:22,104
Inside is her collection,

77
00:09:22,688 --> 00:09:27,734
all gathered through embezzlement,
confiscation, and swapping.

78
00:09:27,818 --> 00:09:29,861
Hey!

79
00:09:29,945 --> 00:09:31,488
How did you obtain this video?

80
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,532
When did you start preparing
to expose this?

81
00:09:33,615 --> 00:09:34,533
Chair Kim!

82
00:09:34,616 --> 00:09:36,034
Is there additional evidence

83
00:09:36,118 --> 00:09:37,869
that Chair Kim Sun-ae
committed this crime?

84
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,376
Even Han Jin-woo,
the artist who painted this work

85
00:09:44,459 --> 00:09:46,420
and was regarded
as a prodigy in the art world,

86
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:49,256
was reduced to a forger
because of Chair Kim.

87
00:09:52,009 --> 00:09:54,803
I stand here today

88
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:59,683
to restore the honor of an artist
who passed away in disgrace.

89
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:01,435
Even at this moment,

90
00:10:01,518 --> 00:10:04,229
another forgery
is likely being created somewhere

91
00:10:04,313 --> 00:10:06,231
under Chair Kim's orders.

92
00:10:06,982 --> 00:10:09,985
Therefore, I urge the police
to conduct a thorough investigation.

93
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:19,995
Hey.

94
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:24,124
Do you think people will believe
a manipulated video?

95
00:10:29,379 --> 00:10:30,213
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

96
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:33,633
You're being arrested under a warrant
for embezzlement, fraud, and violating

97
00:10:33,717 --> 00:10:36,303
the Act on Regulation and Punishment
of Criminal Proceeds Concealment.

98
00:10:37,846 --> 00:10:39,806
-The police seem to believe it.
-Chair Kim.

99
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,475
No, don't.

100
00:10:41,558 --> 00:10:43,352
I didn't do anything wrong. How dare you?

101
00:10:43,435 --> 00:10:45,479
You're making a mistake!

102
00:11:02,621 --> 00:11:03,580
What's all this?

103
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:06,792
Man, an art gallery
doesn't hold a candle to this place.

104
00:11:07,501 --> 00:11:09,086
Just how much did she get away with?

105
00:11:18,637 --> 00:11:20,430
We've already collected evidence
from your suite.

106
00:11:21,098 --> 00:11:22,182
What?

107
00:11:22,265 --> 00:11:24,226
Who do you think you are, going in there?

108
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:25,977
Don't you dare touch a thing!

109
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:27,437
Not a single thing!

110
00:11:27,521 --> 00:11:30,107
Don't touch a thing! It's all mine!

111
00:11:30,941 --> 00:11:32,109
Don't touch anything!

112
00:11:32,192 --> 00:11:33,652
Don't lay a finger on anything!

113
00:11:33,735 --> 00:11:34,569
-It's all mine!
-Come on!

114
00:11:34,653 --> 00:11:35,779
Don't you dare touch anything!

115
00:11:35,862 --> 00:11:37,614
Hey, Han Seol-ah!

116
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:38,782
You!

117
00:11:39,408 --> 00:11:40,867
Han Seol-ah!

118
00:11:44,871 --> 00:11:45,747
Let go of me!

119
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:48,375
Han Seol-ah!

120
00:12:13,442 --> 00:12:16,403
They'll lock down the site
and control access.

121
00:12:17,154 --> 00:12:19,072
There are so many high-value pieces

122
00:12:19,948 --> 00:12:21,450
that they have to seal the vault door

123
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,618
until they can be moved
to a secure location.

124
00:12:24,744 --> 00:12:27,372
We need to compare the documents
you submitted against the evidence.

125
00:12:28,415 --> 00:12:31,793
Could you conduct an initial review
before the professional authentication?

126
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,424
You won't find this painting
in the documents.

127
00:12:37,507 --> 00:12:39,593
The original artist's name
was Han Jin-woo.

128
00:12:40,177 --> 00:12:41,136
He was my father.

129
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:45,807
This piece can be returned, right?

130
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:48,310
Help Seol-ah get it back.

131
00:12:49,019 --> 00:12:49,853
Okay.

132
00:13:00,489 --> 00:13:01,698
What's this?

133
00:13:01,781 --> 00:13:03,283
It's still wrapped.

134
00:13:12,459 --> 00:13:13,502
It's the Stiller.

135
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:16,546
The painting that's worth
over 15 billion won?

136
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:20,425
Did she switch this out too?

137
00:13:21,176 --> 00:13:23,345
It's the original piece that was
on display in the exhibition hall.

138
00:13:25,013 --> 00:13:27,974
Does that mean a forgery of this piece
is being created too?

139
00:13:41,196 --> 00:13:42,822
-Woo-seok.
-I'll call you later.

140
00:14:06,805 --> 00:14:08,098
Are you still at the company?

141
00:14:08,807 --> 00:14:10,016
We need to talk.

142
00:14:12,561 --> 00:14:14,229
Everyone out of the workshop.

143
00:14:14,813 --> 00:14:16,189
Just get out. I'll handle the rest.

144
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:19,359
Just do as I say, you bastards!

145
00:15:34,059 --> 00:15:35,101
What the hell?

146
00:15:35,685 --> 00:15:37,520
Why haven't you left yet?

147
00:15:44,361 --> 00:15:45,570
Who is it?

148
00:15:58,458 --> 00:15:59,584
It's been a while,

149
00:16:00,418 --> 00:16:01,378
Ju Hyun-su.

150
00:16:02,087 --> 00:16:03,171
Damn.

151
00:16:04,005 --> 00:16:06,257
You were the SIU investigator
after the Taemyung pieces?

152
00:16:06,341 --> 00:16:08,385
There's nowhere to run now, you bastard.

153
00:16:08,468 --> 00:16:10,637
Get ready to rot in prison.

154
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:13,306
You have nothing on me
if I burn all the evidence.

155
00:16:14,766 --> 00:16:16,393
Do you want to die too, you bastard?!

156
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:21,648
Goddamn it.

157
00:16:21,731 --> 00:16:23,525
That was a confession, right?

158
00:16:23,608 --> 00:16:25,485
-Damn you.
-That you killed Woo-hee.

159
00:16:25,568 --> 00:16:28,238
My life got screwed because of that bitch!

160
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:30,156
I wouldn't have messed with her
if I'd known her brother was a cop.

161
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,450
Shut the hell up, you asshole!

162
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:35,286
She didn't care about riding in a truck

163
00:16:35,370 --> 00:16:36,871
and begged to ride along on my trips.

164
00:16:37,372 --> 00:16:40,041
She was starved for affection
and so needy.

165
00:16:41,418 --> 00:16:43,211
I said shut the hell up,
you son of a bitch!

166
00:16:58,685 --> 00:16:59,561
Get up.

167
00:17:07,610 --> 00:17:10,739
She was still young,
but said we should get married

168
00:17:10,822 --> 00:17:12,657
so she wouldn't be a burden on you.

169
00:17:12,741 --> 00:17:13,742
Did you know that?

170
00:17:14,909 --> 00:17:17,829
It's your fault she died.

171
00:17:17,912 --> 00:17:19,247
No.

172
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:20,623
That's not true!

173
00:17:22,876 --> 00:17:23,918
You're wrong!

174
00:17:24,002 --> 00:17:25,670
You asshole!

175
00:17:25,754 --> 00:17:26,921
-Die, you son of a bitch!
-Woo-seok!

176
00:17:27,005 --> 00:17:28,715
-Hey, Cha Woo-seok!
-Woo-seok!

177
00:17:29,424 --> 00:17:30,341
Stop!

178
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:33,720
-Stop!
-Woo-seok, stop.

179
00:17:33,803 --> 00:17:34,763
Stop.

180
00:17:36,347 --> 00:17:37,307
Please stop.

181
00:17:45,607 --> 00:17:46,441
Come on.

182
00:17:48,401 --> 00:17:49,277
Let's go.

183
00:18:17,972 --> 00:18:19,349
It's over now.

184
00:18:20,975 --> 00:18:21,851
You can let it go.

185
00:18:30,944 --> 00:18:31,903
It was me.

186
00:18:34,364 --> 00:18:36,199
I was the one who got Woo-hee killed.

187
00:18:37,617 --> 00:18:39,244
It was all me.

188
00:18:43,206 --> 00:18:44,749
Remember what you told me?

189
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:47,460
You said it wasn't my fault.

190
00:18:48,586 --> 00:18:51,130
I'm going to say it back to you.

191
00:18:52,465 --> 00:18:54,175
It wasn't your fault, Woo-seok.

192
00:18:54,968 --> 00:18:55,802
You…

193
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:58,763
always did your best.

194
00:19:42,974 --> 00:19:44,934
Please don't get hurt.

195
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:50,648
You're the only family I have left.

196
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:19,344
It's your fault she died.

197
00:20:34,442 --> 00:20:35,568
Name?

198
00:20:35,652 --> 00:20:36,778
Obviously, Ju Hyun-su.

199
00:20:36,861 --> 00:20:37,904
STATEMENT

200
00:20:37,987 --> 00:20:39,155
Date of birth?

201
00:20:43,201 --> 00:20:46,079
Hey, you think you can pull that
right-to-remain-silent crap on me?

202
00:20:51,834 --> 00:20:52,669
Damn it.

203
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:55,380
This is Cha Woo-hee's case file
that I've kept for six years.

204
00:20:55,463 --> 00:20:58,174
When Cha Woo-seok was raging and pleading

205
00:20:59,592 --> 00:21:01,594
that you were the one
who killed his sister,

206
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:03,513
I just scoffed at him.

207
00:21:04,097 --> 00:21:07,266
I told him he was just being emotional
because the victim was his sister.

208
00:21:07,350 --> 00:21:09,477
There's no way a guy
who's already killed someone

209
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:10,937
has only been making forgeries
all this time.

210
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:13,982
Tell me, you bastard!

211
00:21:14,065 --> 00:21:15,274
What else did Chair Kim make you do?

212
00:21:15,358 --> 00:21:16,734
You killed Paek Jun-beom, didn't you?

213
00:21:16,818 --> 00:21:18,528
No! That wasn't me!

214
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:21,447
Then who did you kill?

215
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:24,117
Did you kill Cha Woo-hee?

216
00:21:26,452 --> 00:21:27,662
Did you kill Kim Yun-ji?

217
00:21:28,997 --> 00:21:31,082
Shit.

218
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:47,432
What's all this?

219
00:21:48,182 --> 00:21:49,976
I wanted to make you something to eat.

220
00:21:50,059 --> 00:21:51,936
You don't have to do that.

221
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:54,063
I know it's hard for you
to be around fire.

222
00:21:54,856 --> 00:21:57,066
It's an induction stove,
so I think I can manage.

223
00:21:58,526 --> 00:21:59,694
You really don't have to.

224
00:22:00,611 --> 00:22:01,904
Should I wash this first?

225
00:22:04,407 --> 00:22:05,992
Go get some rest.

226
00:22:06,075 --> 00:22:07,618
You've been through a lot today.

227
00:22:16,002 --> 00:22:18,921
I'm not good at cooking,

228
00:22:20,506 --> 00:22:23,301
especially when someone is watching me.

229
00:22:40,610 --> 00:22:41,819
CARROT

230
00:22:43,821 --> 00:22:44,947
GREEN ONION

231
00:22:57,001 --> 00:22:58,419
ADD THE BEEF

232
00:23:21,192 --> 00:23:22,860
I can't guarantee it'll taste good.

233
00:23:25,571 --> 00:23:27,198
I've never cooked porridge before.

234
00:23:32,078 --> 00:23:34,831
I thought it'd go down easier
than just rice.

235
00:23:38,835 --> 00:23:39,752
Thank you.

236
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:43,631
It looks great.

237
00:24:04,777 --> 00:24:05,695
It's good.

238
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:15,621
I often thought about the meal

239
00:24:16,914 --> 00:24:18,541
you made for me.

240
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,252
After the interrogation,

241
00:24:21,335 --> 00:24:24,088
when everything inside me fell apart,

242
00:24:25,339 --> 00:24:27,592
the meal that you made me

243
00:24:27,675 --> 00:24:30,011
helped me get back on my feet.

244
00:24:33,931 --> 00:24:35,433
And then you said
you didn't want to see me again.

245
00:24:36,893 --> 00:24:38,186
I was afraid.

246
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:42,356
I thought you might get hurt

247
00:24:43,983 --> 00:24:45,443
if you stayed by my side.

248
00:24:48,821 --> 00:24:49,906
Are you not afraid anymore?

249
00:24:52,450 --> 00:24:54,285
I still am.

250
00:24:56,245 --> 00:24:59,081
But I want to give it a try

251
00:25:00,625 --> 00:25:02,376
because you told me

252
00:25:03,002 --> 00:25:04,545
not to run away,

253
00:25:05,254 --> 00:25:06,631
not to push you away,

254
00:25:08,341 --> 00:25:10,801
and to stay by your side and protect you.

255
00:25:14,263 --> 00:25:17,725
I think I know how you feel right now.

256
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:21,979
But still,

257
00:25:23,147 --> 00:25:24,815
let's keep living.

258
00:25:27,693 --> 00:25:29,987
I won't say things will get better.

259
00:25:31,697 --> 00:25:32,531
Because…

260
00:25:33,658 --> 00:25:36,369
we have to live with this pain
for the rest of our lives.

261
00:25:40,081 --> 00:25:41,332
But let's get through it together.

262
00:25:55,263 --> 00:25:56,222
You should eat.

263
00:25:58,266 --> 00:25:59,392
It's really good.

264
00:26:28,796 --> 00:26:30,589
We ran forensics on Chair Kim's computer

265
00:26:31,132 --> 00:26:33,884
and found chat records with Kim Yun-ji
on the company messenger.

266
00:26:34,635 --> 00:26:36,095
I think you should take a look.

267
00:26:36,178 --> 00:26:37,471
ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER KIM YUN-JI

268
00:26:38,180 --> 00:26:39,807
About the painting my father bought,

269
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:42,601
did you personally bring it in
from New York?

270
00:26:43,185 --> 00:26:44,020
Why do you ask?

271
00:26:44,103 --> 00:26:46,188
Don't you think you crossed the line?

272
00:26:46,272 --> 00:26:48,774
I introduced that painting to him
in good faith.

273
00:26:49,442 --> 00:26:50,776
Come to my suite.

274
00:26:50,860 --> 00:26:52,278
Let's talk in person.

275
00:26:54,739 --> 00:26:55,948
Funny, isn't it?

276
00:26:56,032 --> 00:26:58,909
The head of the NTS investigation bureau
has a daughter who's an auctioneer,

277
00:26:58,993 --> 00:27:01,662
yet has a forgery hanging in his house.

278
00:27:02,246 --> 00:27:04,206
What kind of nonsense is this?

279
00:27:05,374 --> 00:27:07,585
I sent it
for external authentication twice,

280
00:27:07,668 --> 00:27:08,753
but the results were the same.

281
00:27:09,337 --> 00:27:10,671
I wonder what will happen

282
00:27:11,589 --> 00:27:13,507
when my father finds out.

283
00:27:14,091 --> 00:27:15,593
Are you threatening me?

284
00:27:16,844 --> 00:27:18,721
I'm suggesting
we try to solve the problem.

285
00:27:19,805 --> 00:27:20,973
What do you want?

286
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:23,559
The main podium.

287
00:27:27,229 --> 00:27:28,647
In other words, get rid of Ms. Han?

288
00:27:30,399 --> 00:27:32,943
Chair Kim probably felt a lot of pressure.

289
00:27:34,153 --> 00:27:35,654
She would've been hit
with multiple tax evasion charges.

290
00:27:35,738 --> 00:27:38,032
This could've been the motive
for killing Kim Yun-ji.

291
00:27:45,956 --> 00:27:47,917
The Taemyung paintings
that went up in flames

292
00:27:48,709 --> 00:27:51,087
turned up in your secret storage vault,
and you claim ignorance?

293
00:27:52,546 --> 00:27:54,048
My client stored the paintings

294
00:27:54,131 --> 00:27:56,300
upon the client's request.

295
00:27:56,384 --> 00:28:00,346
The issue here is Taemyung's mismanagement
and insurance handling,

296
00:28:00,429 --> 00:28:02,306
not any criminal conduct by my client.

297
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:05,976
Then let's talk about this.

298
00:28:06,602 --> 00:28:09,105
The Stiller is worth over 10 billion won,

299
00:28:09,730 --> 00:28:12,274
and you took advantage
of the owner's death to take it.

300
00:28:14,735 --> 00:28:15,736
It's the same thing.

301
00:28:17,029 --> 00:28:20,449
My client merely kept the painting
safely in the vault

302
00:28:20,533 --> 00:28:23,035
until the inheritance process
was completed.

303
00:28:23,911 --> 00:28:25,079
That's standard practice.

304
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:28,040
Then why did she make a forgery?

305
00:28:29,959 --> 00:28:30,960
Why go through the trouble?

306
00:28:32,711 --> 00:28:35,589
Your lackey, Ju Hyun-su,
has been arrested.

307
00:28:39,218 --> 00:28:41,095
There's no point in holding out,

308
00:28:41,679 --> 00:28:42,513
Ms. Kim Sun-ae.

309
00:28:45,307 --> 00:28:47,143
I don't like your tone.

310
00:28:47,768 --> 00:28:49,353
It's very rude.

311
00:28:50,062 --> 00:28:51,021
Listen, Detective.

312
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:54,066
Did you know who you were dealing with
when you brought me in?

313
00:28:55,651 --> 00:28:59,697
Well, you can't undo a mistake
that's already been made.

314
00:29:00,197 --> 00:29:02,199
Your future in the force

315
00:29:03,451 --> 00:29:06,328
could be an easy road or a difficult one.

316
00:29:06,412 --> 00:29:08,831
This is a critical moment for you.

317
00:29:09,665 --> 00:29:11,167
Don't you get it?

318
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:12,793
Worry about yourself.

319
00:29:13,878 --> 00:29:15,880
Insurance fraud, embezzlement,

320
00:29:15,963 --> 00:29:17,506
dealing in forgeries,

321
00:29:17,590 --> 00:29:18,799
and the cherry on top.

322
00:29:19,675 --> 00:29:20,885
Murder for hire.

323
00:29:27,057 --> 00:29:29,185
You've got some nerve, don't you?

324
00:29:30,144 --> 00:29:31,937
Your lack of gratitude is impressive.

325
00:29:32,021 --> 00:29:33,731
How dare you stab Chair Kim in the back?

326
00:29:35,357 --> 00:29:36,775
What are you really up to?

327
00:29:37,443 --> 00:29:39,778
Is the plan to take over her position
while she's not here?

328
00:29:40,654 --> 00:29:42,406
That's probably what you want to do.

329
00:29:43,282 --> 00:29:45,493
How dare you accuse me of that?

330
00:29:45,576 --> 00:29:46,410
Hey.

331
00:29:47,161 --> 00:29:48,245
I'm not like you.

332
00:29:49,747 --> 00:29:51,373
I'm doing everything I can

333
00:29:51,457 --> 00:29:53,792
to handle the situation from my position.

334
00:29:54,502 --> 00:29:57,129
I have to take responsibility
for what I've done, don't I?

335
00:30:01,842 --> 00:30:02,760
Fine.

336
00:30:03,260 --> 00:30:05,387
I don't know how long you'll last,
but good luck with that.

337
00:30:06,305 --> 00:30:07,848
Chair Kim will be back soon enough.

338
00:30:12,019 --> 00:30:13,979
The remaining auctions
will fall through, right?

339
00:30:14,063 --> 00:30:16,398
These are all the client complaints
we received this morning.

340
00:30:16,482 --> 00:30:18,567
Most of these
are consignment cancellation requests.

341
00:30:18,651 --> 00:30:20,444
This is so annoying.

342
00:30:20,528 --> 00:30:21,695
Give me the list.

343
00:30:21,779 --> 00:30:24,907
I'll personally call the clients
to persuade them.

344
00:30:24,990 --> 00:30:27,993
Ms. Han, I didn't know
you'd come in today.

345
00:30:28,536 --> 00:30:29,370
Are you okay?

346
00:30:29,954 --> 00:30:31,997
I owe you all an apology.

347
00:30:32,081 --> 00:30:36,085
As someone who understands
how deeply you care about Royal Auction,

348
00:30:36,168 --> 00:30:37,670
I'm truly sorry

349
00:30:37,753 --> 00:30:40,047
for causing this situation.

350
00:30:40,881 --> 00:30:42,758
But you did the right thing.

351
00:30:44,635 --> 00:30:47,513
We actually think
this turned out for the better.

352
00:30:48,013 --> 00:30:50,975
We were unknowingly helping Chair Kim
carry out fraud,

353
00:30:51,058 --> 00:30:52,560
so it's a relief
that everything's come to light.

354
00:30:56,522 --> 00:30:58,315
The paintings are safely stored.

355
00:30:58,399 --> 00:31:01,151
How can I trust you after all the talk
of forgery and embezzlement?

356
00:31:01,235 --> 00:31:03,112
I promise to take full responsibility--

357
00:31:03,195 --> 00:31:04,238
I won't stand for this.

358
00:31:04,321 --> 00:31:05,990
I want my artwork back immediately!

359
00:31:06,073 --> 00:31:08,117
-I'll visit you in person.
-I don't care about compensation.

360
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,494
I'll never do business
with you people again!

361
00:31:18,586 --> 00:31:20,838
KIM YEONG-EUN (VVIP)
AFTERNOON CHAMBER MUSIC (BY ELINA)

362
00:31:24,216 --> 00:31:25,968
Ms. Han.

363
00:31:27,011 --> 00:31:28,178
It's about Artist Han Jin-woo.

364
00:31:28,929 --> 00:31:31,056
You said he was family, right?

365
00:31:32,850 --> 00:31:33,684
Yeah.

366
00:31:34,226 --> 00:31:35,436
He was my father.

367
00:31:36,937 --> 00:31:39,607
I didn't know you carried
such a painful memory.

368
00:31:40,899 --> 00:31:43,861
I'm sorry I couldn't do more
to be of support.

369
00:31:44,570 --> 00:31:45,821
Thank you for saying that.

370
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:48,365
I came to work prepared
for people to chew me out,

371
00:31:48,449 --> 00:31:49,992
but you've been so kind.

372
00:31:50,576 --> 00:31:51,410
I can't imagine

373
00:31:52,661 --> 00:31:53,954
how hard it must've been for you.

374
00:31:55,122 --> 00:31:57,499
Things will only get harder for everyone
from here on out.

375
00:31:57,583 --> 00:31:58,709
We'll do whatever it takes.

376
00:31:59,209 --> 00:32:01,295
We're ready for anything.

377
00:32:12,556 --> 00:32:14,558
I thought you were the only one
who really cared.

378
00:32:15,684 --> 00:32:17,144
But it turns out,
Han Seol-ah really cares too.

379
00:32:19,647 --> 00:32:23,734
It gives me chills just imagining
what could've happened if we'd been late.

380
00:32:24,401 --> 00:32:25,402
Make Ju Hyun-su pay

381
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:27,696
for what he did.

382
00:32:29,073 --> 00:32:31,367
The captain is even more furious
about that than I am.

383
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:33,494
I think he feels really guilty.

384
00:32:35,704 --> 00:32:38,248
Have that bastard and Chair Kim
confessed yet?

385
00:32:38,832 --> 00:32:39,792
We'll make them confess.

386
00:32:40,334 --> 00:32:41,710
But do you really think

387
00:32:41,794 --> 00:32:44,380
Chair Kim would kill someone
over a painting?

388
00:32:44,463 --> 00:32:46,924
She's the only suspect
who has a clear motive to kill.

389
00:32:47,007 --> 00:32:48,175
She might not have done it herself,

390
00:32:48,258 --> 00:32:50,010
but she could've hired Ju Hyun-su
to do it.

391
00:32:50,928 --> 00:32:52,763
He was out of the country for a long time,

392
00:32:52,846 --> 00:32:55,683
and there's no reason for Chair Kim
to go after Han Seol-ah's men.

393
00:32:57,726 --> 00:33:00,187
I have my suspicions about Do Eun-hyuk,

394
00:33:00,270 --> 00:33:01,480
but his alibi is solid.

395
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:07,653
CCTV footage shows that Do Eun-hyuk
was at his studio in Cheongun

396
00:33:07,736 --> 00:33:10,322
at the time of Paek Jun-beom's murder.

397
00:33:11,281 --> 00:33:12,616
I want to see it.

398
00:33:12,700 --> 00:33:14,451
Don't ask for official records.

399
00:33:14,535 --> 00:33:17,246
And I want the records
of Paek Jun-beom stalking Han Seol-ah

400
00:33:17,329 --> 00:33:19,164
that were seized from his house,

401
00:33:19,248 --> 00:33:20,833
along with the photos taken in Cheongun.

402
00:33:24,628 --> 00:33:25,546
Please.

403
00:33:43,564 --> 00:33:45,733
Cell tower records show that Do Eun-hyuk
was at his studio in Cheongun

404
00:33:46,275 --> 00:33:48,736
at the time of Paek Jun-beom's murder.

405
00:33:52,448 --> 00:33:54,742
Now I understand

406
00:33:55,993 --> 00:33:57,119
why you trusted Cha Woo-seok.

407
00:33:58,871 --> 00:34:01,331
I never imagined someone like Chair Kim

408
00:34:02,249 --> 00:34:03,792
could get arrested.

409
00:34:04,668 --> 00:34:05,586
That's when it hit me

410
00:34:06,503 --> 00:34:08,338
that you joined hands with Cha Woo-seok

411
00:34:09,423 --> 00:34:12,050
because it wasn't something
I could help you with.

412
00:34:12,968 --> 00:34:14,052
That wasn't why.

413
00:34:15,012 --> 00:34:17,973
There was something we had to do,

414
00:34:18,599 --> 00:34:20,768
and when things overlapped along the way,

415
00:34:22,352 --> 00:34:23,896
we combined our efforts.

416
00:34:26,732 --> 00:34:28,567
That makes your relationship
even more special.

417
00:34:29,318 --> 00:34:30,652
Maybe it was fate.

418
00:34:32,446 --> 00:34:33,655
What do you think of him?

419
00:34:35,866 --> 00:34:37,284
You've got a good eye for people.

420
00:34:47,336 --> 00:34:49,296
He's the kind of person
who belongs in the center of the frame.

421
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:52,841
He's confident and straightforward.

422
00:34:54,218 --> 00:34:55,344
But I'm the opposite.

423
00:34:57,304 --> 00:34:59,556
I'm someone who fits better
outside the frame.

424
00:35:02,726 --> 00:35:06,313
I've acted like it wasn't true
all this time,

425
00:35:08,524 --> 00:35:09,983
but now I'm sure of it.

426
00:35:12,236 --> 00:35:13,695
Why would you think that?

427
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:17,241
People end up living…

428
00:35:19,284 --> 00:35:21,703
the way their hands have been trained.

429
00:35:25,541 --> 00:35:27,501
Anyway, you've been through a lot
to get this far.

430
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:29,545
I'm sure it'll all work out.

431
00:35:30,128 --> 00:35:32,756
And I hope you can get back
Mr. Han's painting.

432
00:35:33,799 --> 00:35:34,925
I still feel uneasy.

433
00:35:35,884 --> 00:35:39,263
Chair Kim isn't the type of person
to take things lying down.

434
00:35:41,515 --> 00:35:42,516
Don't worry.

435
00:35:44,393 --> 00:35:46,186
It'll all work out the way you want.

436
00:36:28,020 --> 00:36:29,104
Ms. Han.

437
00:36:29,187 --> 00:36:30,397
Chair Kim is here.

438
00:36:33,942 --> 00:36:35,027
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

439
00:36:35,110 --> 00:36:38,530
She's not a flight risk
and has health issues?

440
00:36:39,656 --> 00:36:40,908
It's always the same thing.

441
00:36:40,991 --> 00:36:42,743
You've got to be kidding me.

442
00:36:43,327 --> 00:36:44,953
She brought in another top law firm,

443
00:36:45,037 --> 00:36:46,747
and sure enough,
they kept her out of custody.

444
00:37:10,437 --> 00:37:11,396
Take a seat.

445
00:37:20,030 --> 00:37:23,200
What were you thinking all this time
while working here?

446
00:37:23,951 --> 00:37:25,619
Have you been living
with such bitter determination

447
00:37:25,702 --> 00:37:29,539
just to take me down
and get revenge for your father?

448
00:37:30,958 --> 00:37:32,876
I learned it all from you.

449
00:37:39,091 --> 00:37:42,010
My father painted theater signs.

450
00:37:42,970 --> 00:37:45,514
I just helped him paint at first,

451
00:37:45,597 --> 00:37:49,601
but then I wanted to become a real artist,
so I became an apprentice.

452
00:37:50,686 --> 00:37:54,147
That's when I saw your father and realized

453
00:37:56,191 --> 00:38:00,278
that even a prodigy like him
can starve to death in this industry.

454
00:38:01,863 --> 00:38:03,991
Is that why you had him paint forgeries?

455
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:08,870
I gave him a chance to earn a living

456
00:38:08,954 --> 00:38:10,956
so your family wouldn't go hungry.

457
00:38:11,039 --> 00:38:11,915
Hey.

458
00:38:12,416 --> 00:38:14,668
How is it my fault that naive man

459
00:38:14,751 --> 00:38:17,129
went into debt to repay everything?

460
00:38:17,713 --> 00:38:21,091
Do you think that justifies
causing someone's death?

461
00:38:21,174 --> 00:38:24,136
I didn't cause it! It was his choice!

462
00:38:24,219 --> 00:38:28,724
I was the one who called 119
when your house caught on fire.

463
00:38:28,807 --> 00:38:30,600
I was the one who saved your life!

464
00:38:30,684 --> 00:38:32,602
You should've left me to die!

465
00:38:35,105 --> 00:38:37,149
Then I wouldn't be in so much pain.

466
00:38:38,358 --> 00:38:40,777
I had to grovel before you like a dog

467
00:38:41,361 --> 00:38:43,864
and constantly force a smile

468
00:38:43,947 --> 00:38:45,782
for living at the price
of my parents' lives.

469
00:38:48,827 --> 00:38:50,287
Even if you manage to get out of this,

470
00:38:51,788 --> 00:38:54,374
I'll hunt you down to the very end.

471
00:38:59,212 --> 00:39:00,756
What else can you possibly do?

472
00:39:01,923 --> 00:39:04,801
All the judges and prosecutors
are in my pocket.

473
00:39:05,969 --> 00:39:09,056
A dog might get away
with biting its owner once,

474
00:39:09,556 --> 00:39:10,390
but do it again,

475
00:39:11,349 --> 00:39:13,268
and it'll be beaten to death.

476
00:39:15,854 --> 00:39:18,315
I'll have to go for the neck, then.

477
00:39:22,027 --> 00:39:24,321
You think you'll get a chance to do that?

478
00:39:24,988 --> 00:39:28,241
It'll be your neck on the line.

479
00:39:33,413 --> 00:39:34,706
I guess

480
00:39:35,540 --> 00:39:37,584
we'll just have to wait and see…

481
00:39:40,170 --> 00:39:41,630
whose neck is on the line.

482
00:40:24,422 --> 00:40:25,882
Ju Hyun-su will be out soon.

483
00:40:26,424 --> 00:40:28,677
Take care of that bastard quietly first.

484
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:29,761
If you don't,

485
00:40:31,429 --> 00:40:34,641
I'll make sure she finds out
about the secret

486
00:40:34,724 --> 00:40:36,476
you're so desperate to keep from her.

487
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:10,343
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

488
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:40,373
And even if it costs me my life, Llorona

489
00:41:43,168 --> 00:41:47,964
I will not stop loving you

490
00:42:10,779 --> 00:42:12,030
…Llorona…

491
00:42:17,827 --> 00:42:23,375
Ah, woe is me, Llorona, Llorona

492
00:42:28,713 --> 00:42:33,718
Ah, woe is me, Llorona, Llorona

493
00:43:02,539 --> 00:43:08,420
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

494
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:53,506
Everything is too perfect.

495
00:44:16,738 --> 00:44:17,572
Where are you going?

496
00:44:20,492 --> 00:44:21,534
To see Chair Kim.

497
00:44:22,118 --> 00:44:23,161
Did she ask to see you?

498
00:44:23,912 --> 00:44:24,746
No.

499
00:44:26,414 --> 00:44:28,041
I'm telling her that I'm quitting.

500
00:44:29,751 --> 00:44:31,419
I wanted to take responsibility

501
00:44:32,587 --> 00:44:35,048
and make things right
regarding the last auction,

502
00:44:35,548 --> 00:44:37,384
-but Chair Kim--
-She'd never let that slide.

503
00:44:38,635 --> 00:44:39,511
Let's go together.

504
00:44:39,594 --> 00:44:41,137
I'm quitting too.

505
00:44:41,930 --> 00:44:44,057
I told you not to do that.

506
00:44:44,140 --> 00:44:45,100
Don't get it wrong.

507
00:44:45,850 --> 00:44:47,685
I want to focus on my own work now

508
00:44:47,769 --> 00:44:49,396
and get back in the water.

509
00:47:02,779 --> 00:47:03,905
The security guard said

510
00:47:03,988 --> 00:47:05,907
he heard music playing
into the early hours.

511
00:47:06,533 --> 00:47:08,660
The first to discover her
were Han Seol-ah and Do Eun-hyuk.

512
00:47:08,743 --> 00:47:10,870
-Any signs of foul play?
-Not yet.

513
00:47:11,454 --> 00:47:13,790
There's a suicide note on her laptop,

514
00:47:13,873 --> 00:47:15,917
but it's not enough
to rule this a suicide.

515
00:47:16,417 --> 00:47:19,128
The CCTVs near the suite don't work.

516
00:47:20,630 --> 00:47:22,882
Well, she had to move the paintings
into the storage vault secretly.

517
00:47:24,425 --> 00:47:25,802
And now her death

518
00:47:26,469 --> 00:47:27,512
has become a secret too.

519
00:47:33,309 --> 00:47:35,728
HAN SEOL-AH

520
00:47:35,812 --> 00:47:38,481
Your call cannot be connected.

521
00:48:58,770 --> 00:49:01,689
This isn't the outcome I was hoping for.

522
00:49:02,899 --> 00:49:05,526
Chair Kim would never commit suicide.

523
00:49:05,610 --> 00:49:07,528
When I saw her the day before,

524
00:49:07,612 --> 00:49:09,364
she showed no signs of guilt

525
00:49:09,447 --> 00:49:10,907
and was self-assured.

526
00:49:12,492 --> 00:49:15,453
I think someone went through
the chair's suite.

527
00:49:17,789 --> 00:49:20,416
And it's strange that she left
the suicide note on her laptop,

528
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:24,379
considering that she still keeps
handwritten ledgers.

529
00:49:28,633 --> 00:49:30,176
Does that mean Chair Kim was also…

530
00:49:31,761 --> 00:49:33,179
It's all connected.

531
00:49:34,847 --> 00:49:35,973
I feel like

532
00:49:37,100 --> 00:49:38,976
this is all the work of one person.

533
00:49:39,852 --> 00:49:41,604
This isn't over

534
00:49:42,188 --> 00:49:43,731
until we catch the killer.

535
00:49:54,826 --> 00:49:55,868
Are you okay?

536
00:49:57,954 --> 00:49:59,163
You'll hurt yourself. I'll do it.

537
00:50:26,232 --> 00:50:27,150
Dear Seol-ah,

538
00:50:28,443 --> 00:50:31,654
I hope the day you read this never comes.

539
00:50:33,740 --> 00:50:35,116
A woman came to see me

540
00:50:36,159 --> 00:50:37,952
and told me some strange things about you.

541
00:50:39,704 --> 00:50:41,205
To be honest, I was swayed by her words.

542
00:50:54,761 --> 00:50:56,429
This is Seung-jae's handwriting.

543
00:50:59,307 --> 00:51:00,975
He left a clue about the culprit.

544
00:51:14,822 --> 00:51:15,865
Are you okay?

545
00:51:19,076 --> 00:51:19,952
Seol-ah.

546
00:51:46,604 --> 00:51:47,563
INSURANCE APPLICATION FORM

547
00:51:48,815 --> 00:51:50,900
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

548
00:51:57,573 --> 00:51:59,700
This is your parents'
life insurance application form.

549
00:52:01,828 --> 00:52:03,329
Look at the agent's name.

550
00:52:05,331 --> 00:52:06,749
I think it might be someone you know.

551
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:08,167
INSURANCE AGENT: KIM MI-SUK

552
00:52:22,473 --> 00:52:24,392
These are photos
from Paek Jun-beom's house.

553
00:52:25,726 --> 00:52:27,061
I hadn't looked closely before,

554
00:52:27,562 --> 00:52:29,021
but Kim Yun-ji was in some of them.

555
00:52:33,359 --> 00:52:34,944
So she was in Cheongun

556
00:52:35,736 --> 00:52:37,488
the day before Seung-jae died.

557
00:52:38,489 --> 00:52:39,866
She stayed until the next morning.

558
00:52:43,286 --> 00:52:45,997
This photo
was taken by the river that day.

559
00:52:55,298 --> 00:52:58,301
Kim Yun-ji was a witness.

560
00:53:00,303 --> 00:53:02,430
She knew who killed Seung-jae.

561
00:53:03,514 --> 00:53:05,141
And that's why she was killed.

562
00:53:09,562 --> 00:53:11,397
Can this be used as evidence?

563
00:53:11,898 --> 00:53:13,357
It's not enough,

564
00:53:14,317 --> 00:53:15,776
but they'll show up in front of me soon

565
00:53:16,819 --> 00:53:18,154
because I'm Han Seol-ah's man

566
00:53:18,988 --> 00:53:20,281
who knows their secret.

567
00:53:21,365 --> 00:53:22,617
If we use this opportunity to--

568
00:53:22,700 --> 00:53:23,534
No.

569
00:53:23,618 --> 00:53:25,703
I won't use you as bait.

570
00:53:25,786 --> 00:53:29,498
I'm the only one who can approach them
without raising suspicion.

571
00:53:29,582 --> 00:53:31,500
-I'll do it.
-It's too dangerous.

572
00:53:31,584 --> 00:53:32,752
Even Chair Kim is dead.

573
00:53:32,835 --> 00:53:34,003
What's dangerous

574
00:53:34,086 --> 00:53:37,048
is always feeling on edge
and shaking in fear.

575
00:53:37,131 --> 00:53:38,883
I won't live like that anymore.

576
00:53:38,966 --> 00:53:40,384
Then let's go together.

577
00:53:40,468 --> 00:53:41,928
We'll get caught if we do.

578
00:53:45,681 --> 00:53:48,184
You need to confirm something too, right?

579
00:53:49,435 --> 00:53:50,436
Then at least tell me your route.

580
00:53:51,354 --> 00:53:53,272
I'll also keep you updated
whenever I'm on the move.

581
00:53:56,776 --> 00:53:57,693
Be careful.

582
00:54:08,955 --> 00:54:11,332
I have my suspicions about Do Eun-hyuk,

583
00:54:11,415 --> 00:54:12,667
but his alibi is solid.

584
00:54:13,209 --> 00:54:15,670
Records show that Do Eun-hyuk
was at his studio in Cheongun

585
00:54:15,753 --> 00:54:17,505
at the time of Paek Jun-beom's murder.

586
00:54:50,454 --> 00:54:53,290
CHEONGUN STUDIO

587
00:54:54,875 --> 00:54:57,044
RECOMMENDED ROUTE
16 MINUTES

588
00:54:58,587 --> 00:55:00,131
If I drive as fast as possible…

589
00:55:51,724 --> 00:55:53,934
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

590
00:56:10,159 --> 00:56:12,411
BOOKKEEPING LEDGER

591
00:56:38,562 --> 00:56:40,773
DO EUN-HYUK

592
00:57:00,042 --> 00:57:01,585
If there's no traffic,

593
00:57:01,669 --> 00:57:05,214
it's possible to get to the studio
from Paek Jun-beom's villa in 15 minutes.

594
00:57:59,518 --> 00:58:00,728
PHOTO EQUIPMENT PURCHASE

595
00:58:00,811 --> 00:58:01,896
LIVING EXPENSES

596
00:58:01,979 --> 00:58:03,397
DO EUN-HYE PRIVATE TUTORING EXPENSES

597
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:04,773
LIVING EXPENSES

598
00:58:06,901 --> 00:58:08,527
EQUIPMENT PURCHASE

599
00:58:25,377 --> 00:58:26,962
LICENSE CERTIFICATION
DO EUN-HYE TUITION

600
00:58:27,046 --> 00:58:29,423
DARKROOM & LARGE TANK INSTALLATION
SOUNDPROOFING WORK

601
00:59:50,921 --> 00:59:52,256
I'm going to Cheongun.

602
00:59:52,339 --> 00:59:54,425
CHA WOO-SEOK

603
01:00:00,055 --> 01:00:01,056
Don't worry.

604
01:00:02,725 --> 01:00:04,685
It'll all work out the way you want.

605
01:00:31,545 --> 01:00:32,838
Do Eun-hyuk.

606
01:01:18,509 --> 01:01:20,010
If you love Han Seol-ah…

607
01:01:21,470 --> 01:01:22,596
you die.

608
01:01:26,058 --> 01:01:27,559
I didn't gain anything.

609
01:01:27,643 --> 01:01:28,685
Watch out!

610
01:01:28,769 --> 01:01:29,937
I only lost.

611
01:01:31,271 --> 01:01:33,148
If the culprit thinks I'm your man,

612
01:01:33,732 --> 01:01:34,691
I'll either die…

613
01:01:36,402 --> 01:01:38,070
or find out who the real culprit is.

614
01:01:38,153 --> 01:01:40,030
What if you really die?

615
01:01:40,114 --> 01:01:41,115
I don't care.

616
01:01:41,198 --> 01:01:42,491
Go ahead and use me.

617
01:01:43,575 --> 01:01:45,577
This isn't over

618
01:01:46,370 --> 01:01:47,913
until we catch the killer.

619
01:01:48,580 --> 01:01:50,499
They'll show up in front of me soon

620
01:01:50,582 --> 01:01:51,834
because I'm Han Seol-ah's man

621
01:01:52,459 --> 01:01:53,919
who knows their secret.

622
01:01:55,379 --> 01:01:57,381
Subtitle: Jenny Kim

